column19: My name is Youyou Xu. I am a student at the Haas School of Business at the University of California at Berkeley. I would like to invite you to take part in my research study which compares overconfident behavior of humans versus neural network models. If you agree to take part you will be asked to respond to a short survey. In this survey you will be asked to read about some scenarios and make judgments.The entire exercise should take around 5 minutes. There is no direct benefit to you anticipated from participating in this study. However we hope that the information gained from the study will help us better understand how people and machine learning algorithms think overconfidently. There is little risk to you from taking part in this research. As with all research there is a chance that confidentiality could be compromised; however we are taking precautions to minimize this risk. Your study data will be handled as confidentially as possible. This survey will code the data with ID numbers so that each participant’s answers cannot be linked to their identities.Please understand that participation in research is completely voluntary. You are free to decline to take part in the project. You can decline to answer any questions and are free to stop taking part in the project at any time. If you have any questions about the research you may contact me by e-mail at williamxyy@berkeley.edu. If you have any questions regarding your treatment or rights as a participant in this research project please contact the University of California at Berkeley’s Committee for Protection of Human Subjects at (510) 642-7461 subjects@berkeley.edu.

column23: Introduction. In this survey you will be asked to predict the brand of cars by looking at their images. There are only 5 possible options: Audi BMW Chevrolet Dodge and Ford.- You will first complete 2 study phases. In these phases you will see images of cars guess the brand and then see the true answer immediately.- Then you'll begin 1 test phase. In this phase you'll see 10 images of cars. For each image please rate your confidence in your answer using a number between 0 and 1 (e.g. 0.75) where higher values indicate greater confidence.- For example you could assign confidence scores: (Audi: 0.80 BWM: 0.20 Chevrolet: 0.00 Dodge: 0.00 Ford: 0.00). In this case you believe Audi is most likely the true answer.
